item.title: Creating a New Theme
item.description: Introduction This tutorial will show you how to create a simple theme in Hugo. I assume that you are familiar with HTML, the bash command line, and that you are comfortable using Markdown to format content. I’ll explain how Hugo uses templates and how you can organize your templates to create a theme. I won’t cover using CSS to style your theme. We’ll start with creating a new site with a very basic template.

item.title: Time-complexity
item.description: from https://wiki.python.org/moin/TimeComplexity This page documents the time-complexity (aka “Big O” or “Big Oh”) of various operations in current CPython. Other Python implementations (or older or still-under development versions of CPython) may have slightly different performance characteristics. However, it is generally safe to assume that they are not slower by more than a factor of O(log n). Generally, ‘n’ is the number of elements currently in the container. ‘k’ is either the value of a parameter or the number of elements in the parameter.
